latestIgtvVideos.title: Morning Practice
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Today I woke up little late from my usual time. I had only 15 minutes for yoga practice. My practice time is 6 am to 7 am. I have fixed a corner on my terrace for daily practice and the same corner is favorite of a peacock who comes there at 7 am daily to pick some grains and dance happily. I started my practice at 6:45 am and at 7:00 am peacock was waiting for his place to be vacated. So after doing few rounds of sun salutation, I concluded my practice with:
1. Dolphin pushup with chaturanga(3sets for 1 minute) 
2. Handstand hold (15 seconds hold 3sets) 
#yogapractice #handstandresolution #strengthening #yogagirl #yogalove #yogaeverywhere #yogasequence #fitnessmotivation #peacock #naturelover #yogatime #yogafeature #yogastrong #fitfam #yoga #fitnessjourney

latestPosts.caption:
HYROX Delhi 2025 🏃🏽‍♂️

What an experience this was. Competing in HYROX wasn’t just about crossing the finish line – it was about showing up for ourselves and each other. From running laps with legs that felt like stone to pushing sleds heavier than us, every moment tested our limits.

Honestly, there were times when we thought, “Why are we even doing this to ourselves?” But then you hear your partner cheering you on, you see other athletes fighting their own battles, and you find that last bit of energy to keep moving.

This race taught us so much – about teamwork, patience, and never giving up even when your body says it’s done. It reminded us why we train every day, why we wake up early, and why discipline matters more than motivation.

We showed up, gave it our all, and left with sore bodies but stronger minds. 💪🏽

If you’re training for anything in life right now, remember this – the finish line is just a moment. What really matters is everything you become on the way to it.

HYROX – done and dusted ✔️ Now, time to recover and come back stronger for whatever’s next.

These last two months have been a true test of willpower and dedication at Calination.

From day one, it wasn’t just about training for HYROX. It was about building stronger bodies, sharper minds, and unbreakable spirits.

We focused on every aspect –
 Endurance runs to build that engine
  Strength sessions to handle every station with power
  HYROX circuits to prepare for fatigue and transitions
  Mindset work to build confidence and race readiness

There were days filled with sweat, struggle, and self-doubt, but each of you chose to show up, push through, and rise stronger. That’s what makes champions.

Tomorrow is showtime. 
Remember, the hard work is already done. Now it’s about trusting your training, staying calm under pressure, and giving it everything you’ve got.

All the best to all  athletes racing tomorrow. You’ve earned this moment. Step on that HYROX floor with pride and leave with no regrets. We are already proud of you. 🇮🇳 

#Calination #HYROXprep #RaceDay #StrongerTogether #Unbreakable #TrustTheProcess"
